This scenario comes from a comment in https://github.com/xamarin/xamarin-android/issues/3387#issuecomment-514913521 that was unrelated to the original symptom of that issue.

### Steps to reproduce

 1. Build and install the attached test case:

    ```
    msbuild -restore -p:AndroidUseAapt2=true -t:Install
    ```

 2. Run the app on the device.

Test case: [Aapt2IncorrectStyleableIds.zip](https://github.com/xamarin/xamarin-android/files/3438683/Aapt2IncorrectStyleableIds.zip)

### Expected behavior

If you build and install with AAPT instead of AAPT2 (`-p:AndroidUseAapt2=false`), the text view in the middle of the app screen shows:

> Custom attribute text

The relevant excerpt from *Resource.designer.cs* is:

```
// aapt resource value: 0
public const int ElevenAttributes_attr00 = 0;

// aapt resource value: 1
public const int ElevenAttributes_attr01 = 1;

// aapt resource value: 2
public const int ElevenAttributes_attr02 = 2;

// aapt resource value: 3
public const int ElevenAttributes_attr03 = 3;

// aapt resource value: 4
public const int ElevenAttributes_attr04 = 4;

// aapt resource value: 5
public const int ElevenAttributes_attr05 = 5;

// aapt resource value: 6
public const int ElevenAttributes_attr06 = 6;

// aapt resource value: 7
public const int ElevenAttributes_attr07 = 7;

// aapt resource value: 8
public const int ElevenAttributes_attr08 = 8;

// aapt resource value: 9
public const int ElevenAttributes_attr09 = 9;

// aapt resource value: 10
public const int ElevenAttributes_attr10 = 10;
```

### Actual behavior

The search bar in the middle of the app screen is empty and doesn't show any placeholder text.

The relevant excerpt from *Resource.designer.cs* is:

```
// aapt resource value: 0x0
public const int ElevenAttributes_attr00 = 0;

// aapt resource value: 0x1
public const int ElevenAttributes_attr01 = 1;

// aapt resource value: 0x2
public const int ElevenAttributes_attr02 = 2;

// aapt resource value: 0x3
public const int ElevenAttributes_attr03 = 3;

// aapt resource value: 0x4
public const int ElevenAttributes_attr04 = 4;

// aapt resource value: 0x5
public const int ElevenAttributes_attr05 = 5;

// aapt resource value: 0x6
public const int ElevenAttributes_attr06 = 6;

// aapt resource value: 0x7
public const int ElevenAttributes_attr07 = 7;

// aapt resource value: 0x8
public const int ElevenAttributes_attr08 = 8;

// aapt resource value: 0x9
public const int ElevenAttributes_attr09 = 9;

// aapt resource value: 0x10
public const int ElevenAttributes_attr10 = 16;
```

### Version Information

The bad behavior when using `-p:AndroidUseAapt2=true` is the same for:

Xamarin.Android 9.5.0.27
Xamarin.Android 9.4.0.51
